SystemPhoto: Annelie Anticevich Planting a tree to mark the Christmas party for orphans occasion (from left) Headman Sipho Masua, Father Richard Bedingsfeld, Inkosi s wife Nomusa Xolo, a visitor and on the far right is Inkosi Xolo. Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories ORPHANS and vulnerable children from Sithandisizwe in Izingolweni could not hide their excitement as they enjoyed a Christmas party organised for them on 16 December. Inkosi Xolo was a guest of honor and his keynote speech he stressed the importance of education. He told the children that he expected them to work very hard on their studies in the new year. The Inkosi then planted a tree to commemorate the occasion before he and his wife awarded trophies to children who excelled in education and sport this year. - Supplied.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.